imagine we have a bug on signup form,
we create new branch to working on it in isolated area!
in next lessons we will merge it.


1.git branch bugfix

2.git branch -m bugfix bugfix/signup-form   //renaming this new branch
                                            //to better name

3.git switch bugfix/signup-form             //we can use "checkout" command
                                            //but checkout has some other application (it's move head pointer)
                                            //so it is better to use "switch" to switch branch.

4.imagine we add some line on "branches 1" file,
  to solve the bug!
  we commit this lines on bugfix/signup-form  branch
  (so these lines not accessible on main branch
   our working directory changed through branches)

Note: Mosh use venus folder (we have it in section3),
      but because it is submodule, we can not see inside commit
      from here, so we use "branches 1" file.

